"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-03-parisolympics-sixth-place-jamaican-mixed-4x400m-relay-team\", \"text\": \"KINGSTON, Jamaica- Jamaica finished fifth in the mixed 4x400m relays on Saturday's third day of the track and field schedule at the Olympic Games at Stade de France in Paris running 3:11.67.  The performance was an improvement on their seventh place finish three years ago in Tokyo, Japan.  The team initially finished in sixth place but was moved up a position after France was disqualified.  The Jamaicans fielded an unchanged team from the one that qualified on Friday with\\u00a0Reheem Hayles, Junelle Bromfield, Zandrion Barnes and Stephenie Ann McPherson battling a powerful field.  They ran slower than the national record 3:11.06 seconds.  A majestic anchor leg run from superstar Femke Bol who got the baton in fourth place, took the Netherlands team to victory in a European Area Record 3:07.43 seconds, ahead of the USA who set a world record on Friday with Great Britain third in 3:08.01 seconds.  -Paul A Reid  HOUSE RULES\"}"